              <p class="text-sm font-black text-[#F5521A] uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE PROBLEM</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Contacted Framer support for refund on remaining 9 months. Response: "Annual plans are non-refundable." Options: Eat the $187.50 loss or stay locked into platform that can't do what client needs. The "savings" of $60 vs monthly pricing became a $187.50 trap. Annual billing discount: -$60. Lock-in cost: +$127.50 net loss.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="border-l-[3px] border-[#F5521A] pl-5 py-4 bg-white rounded-r">
              <p class="text-sm font-black text-[#F5521A] uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE FIX</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Now Elena starts with monthly plans on every new AI builder, even though they cost 17-23% more. Treats first 2-3 months as extended trial. Only switches to annual after 6 months of confirmed fit. Lost $187.50 once. Saved $1,200+ since by avoiding lock-in on 4 projects that needed to pivot.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="border-l-[3px] border-[#F5521A] pl-5 py-4 bg-white rounded-r">
